1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,730
Buyer evidence is not what the rep

2
00:00:01,780 --> 00:00:02,160
believes.

3
00:00:02,220 --> 00:00:04,300
It is what the buyer said or did.

4
00:00:05,050 --> 00:00:06,590
There is a difference between a rep

5
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:08,730
saying the champion is engaged and a

6
00:00:08,790 --> 00:00:10,680
buyer saying in a recorded call that

7
00:00:10,730 --> 00:00:12,740
this problem is costing us two million

8
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:14,670
dollars a year and we need to fix it

9
00:00:14,710 --> 00:00:15,360
before Q3.

10
00:00:15,410 --> 00:00:16,090
One is an opinion.

11
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:17,880
One is evidence.

12
00:00:18,340 --> 00:00:20,220
AI can help teams build an evidence

13
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,170
standard by surfacing what was actually

14
00:00:22,220 --> 00:00:24,750
said in calls, what actions the buyer

15
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,140
took, what stakeholders showed up, and

16
00:00:27,220 --> 00:00:28,460
what questions were asked.

17
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:30,850
When managers inspect deals using

18
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:32,840
evidence instead of rep confidence, the

19
00:00:32,890 --> 00:00:34,810
pipeline becomes more accurate.

20
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,830
The forecast becomes more reliable.

21
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,030
Coaching becomes more specific.

22
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,170
The shift is not complicated.

23
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:44,670
It requires deciding that buyer evidence

24
00:00:44,740 --> 00:00:46,290
matters more than seller optimism.

25
00:00:47,420 --> 00:00:50,250
Follow A-Gent for the agent-first GTM

26
00:00:50,310 --> 00:00:50,740
playbook.
